1. Project Title
Library Management System
2. Problem Statement
In many libraries, book records, issue details, and return details are maintained manually. This process is time-consuming and can lead to errors such as misplaced records, difficulty in tracking books, and delays in issuing or returning books. A Library Management System is required to automate these activities and efficiently manage library operations.
3. Objective
To automate library management activities.
To maintain book and student/member records.
To simplify book issue and return processes.
To track available and borrowed books.
To reduce manual work and improve accuracy.
To generate reports quickly and efficiently.
Modules
1. Admin Module
Manage books
Manage students
View reports
System monitoring
2. Book Inventory Module
Add books
Update book details
Remove books
Track book availability
3. Member Management Module
Register members
Update member information
Maintain member records
4. Book Search Module
Search books by title
Search by author
Search by category
Check availability
5. Book Issue Module
Issue books to members
Set due dates
Record transactions
6. Book Return Module
Return books
Calculate fines
Update availability status
7. Fine Management Module
Calculate overdue fines
Maintain fine records
Generate fine reports
8. Report Module
Book issue report
Return report
Member report
Fine collection report
